      "content": "Oh, my bad, I thought you were attached to the file. Here is the text from Section 4.2: \n\n\"4.2 Price Adjustments: The Supplier reserves the right to implement a price increase of up to 5% during peak demand months (June, July, August) without prior written consent from the Client, provided the Supplier gives 7 days' notice via email.\"\n\nSo, looking at that, am I safe? Can they just hike the price on us without us actually signing off on it? Like I said, we really can't afford any surprises in the budget.",
